SQL is a platform for relational structured databases or data that can be organized in tables. It is a domain specific language and was introduced in the 1970s. It consists of Data query Language (DQL), Data Definition Language (DDL), Data Control Language (DCL), and Data Manipulation Language (DML).
SQL works on the principle of CRUD (Create, Read, Update and Delete) 
SQL is one of the first languages that employs the relational model
SQL was initially developed by IBM and it is now been bought over by Oracle Corporation
